{"blocks":[{"key":"2b36d","text":"Aspirate the medium from plates, wash by dispensing 100 µl DPBS per well using a Multichannel pipette. Gently swirl plates to wash the content of the wells.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6qrc0","text":"Aspirate DPBS from the plates using multichannel aspirator.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7s5v8","text":"Add 25 µl Trypsin to each well using a Multichannel pipette. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e1qpk","text":"Incubate at      ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":13,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":15,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"5o0po","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"049DCD607DA111ECB567D7C090A77204","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"37","unit":10}},"1":{"type":"duration","mutability":"","data":{"duration":300,"guid":"06BE15507DA111ECB567D7C090A77204","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cjk1b","text":"Take a new 96-well MEFs plate. Aspirate MEF medium and add 75 µl of hPSCs medium + Rock inhibitor to the wells. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fob1q","text":"Take the Trypsin-dissociated cells out from 37°C . Dispense 25 µl hPSCs medium + Rock inhibitor onto each well using a Multichannel pipette to inactivate trypsin. Or else, use fresh pipette tips for each well.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eciv1","text":"Use a fresh 200 µl filter tip box for this step: ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"s5cs","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6r11u","text":"Set the Multichannel at 25 µl, load it with pipette tips, break down the trypsinized wells by pipette at least 7-8 times, focusing mostly on the center of the well, also pipette 2-3 times near the circumference of the wells. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cetqg","text":"Using the same tips, take out 25 µl of the dissociated cells, and dispense them over the new MEFs plate from step 8. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2rogj","text":"Take the same tips to pipette out the remaining approx. 25 µl cell suspension to the PCR plate from step 7. This becomes the gDNA plate. The location for all wells on tissue culture plate should correspond with their particular gDNA collection plate. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9il0l","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2hdd7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d4onk","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"25pit","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"3j7si","text":"Throughout steps 10-12, make sure to use fresh tips for each well. Also make sure to prioritize adding the first 25 µl of cells to the new tissue culture plate , and then go back to collect the remaining 25 µl to be added to gDNA plate.
